narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments:
Statistics: models and probability events, as well as testing data through stats
Economics: how different economics theories prove to hold
Data analysis: Learned how to program in R and use that code as evidence to determine statistical connections regarding economic models and theories
I learned how to understand R-code, and learned how to break down big data sets for analysis. I also learned how to think like a data scientist which is helpful when studying these large data sets.
Coding skills
I learned about data science, probability, and statistics in terms of economic issues. I gained the skill of coding in the R program and improved my mathematical and critical thinking skills.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths: teaching methods, constructive, organized
Weaknesses: N/A

Strengths: I like the format of the course where the videos are about the fundamentals and the problem sets involve R-code applications. A weakness is that there could be extra math practice problems.
Biggest strength is the teaching of practical skills that will be useful in the future. Weakness is the pace it has to go at because of the sheer amount of material that has to be covered.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes
I would recommend this course to another student if they want to get a sense of what it is like to analyze and interpret data. Also, the course provides basic exposure to R.
Yes I would recommend this course to another student because of the skills it teaches but I would warn them that they must be fully committed to taking it.

narratives.question_text: How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: I will use a lot of R coding and data analyzing to determine financial issues

This course provides strong fundamentals for more advanced data analysis courses and gives me a taste of what it is like to think like a data analyst. I plan on doing something with data in the future, so this course was a good introduction.
Coding and data science

I think coding will be useful in a world where technology continues to dominate more and more of everyday life. The critical thinking skills of a data scientist will also be very useful across disciplines.
